## ⚙️ Hardware Specifications

| Parameter       | Value                |
| --------------- | -------------------- |
| Microcontroller | ATmega328P-AU        |
| Clock Frequency | 16 MHz               |
| Input Voltage   | 5V / 12V             |
| Logic Levels    | 5V / 3.3V            |
| Communication   | UART                 |
| Programming     | ICSP                 |
| PCB Layers      | 2 Layer              |
| Form Factor     | Custom Compact Board |

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### 🔧 1. Burn Bootloader

Use an ICSP programmer to flash the Arduino bootloader.

### 💻 2. Upload Code

* Connect via USB-UART / FTDI
* Select **Arduino UNO** in Arduino IDE
* Upload sketches

### 🔌 3. Power the Board

* USB Type-C (5V)
* Barrel Jack (12V)

---

## 🔌 Pin Configuration

| Category | Pins            |
| -------- | --------------- |
| Digital  | D0 – D13        |
| Analog   | A0 – A5         |
| UART     | TX / RX         |
| Power    | 5V / 3.3V / GND |

